{{see also|D-Link DIR-615|SGE}}
The FCC docs state that this device will be sold as :the GO-RT-N300, DIR-617, and the DIR-615S1. The device is using a square chip package RTL8196x :(RTL8196D / RTL8196E, presumably).
Two different power adapters are shown in the FCC photos... *'''Shenzhen Frecom Electronics Co., Ltd.''' F05W-120050SPAU :(100-240VAC ~ 50/60Hz, 190mA -> 12VDC, 0.5A) *'''Shenzhen Gongjin Electronics Co., Ltd.''' S06A22-120A050-PB :(100-240VAC ~ 50/60Hz, max. 0.3A -> 12VDC, 0.5A)
